Pages Where Emails Are Now Integrated
Based on the updated services, here’s a list of pages/components that now trigger emails automatically when certain actions occur.

1. Inquiries Management (Inquiries page)
createInquiry → sends inquiry_confirmation to the parent/student.

scheduleDemo → sends demo_scheduled to the parent/student.

rejectInquiry → sends inquiry_status_change (with rejection reason).

updateInquiry (when status changes) → sends inquiry_status_change with old/new status.

These are called from the Inquiries page (and possibly from InquiryForm modal).

2. Admission Conversion (StudentManagement or dedicated “Convert to Student” button)
convertInquiryToStudent → sends admission_confirmation to the parent/student.

This is typically used in a page where an inquiry is converted into a student (e.g., StudentManagement or a button inside Inquiries).

3. Students (Students page)
createStudent → sends account_welcome to the student’s email (if provided).

4. Parents (Parents page)
createParent → sends account_activation to the parent (with login credentials).

5. Teachers (Teachers page)
createTeacher → sends teacher_onboarding to the teacher’s email.

6. Batches / Student Batch Assignment (StudentBatches page)
assignStudentToBatch, bulkAssignStudents, updateStudentBatch (when batch changes) → sends batch_change to the student/parent.

7. Attendance Reports (AttendanceReports page)
sendAttendanceReportEmail (explicitly called) → sends the report via email (HTML table) to specified recipients. This is a manual action, but you can add a button to trigger it.

8. Certificates (Certificates page)
createCertificate → sends certificate_issued to the student/parent.

9. Exams (Exams page)
createExam → sends exam_schedule to all active students in the batch.

10. Homework (Homework page)
createHomework → sends new_homework to all active students in the batch.

11. Fee Payments / Fee Management (Fees page, CollectPaymentModal)
collectPayment and collectPaymentWithInvoice → sends fee_receipt to the student/parent.

12. Income & Expenses (Income, Expenses pages)
createIncome and createExpense → sends system_announcement to all admins.

13. Leaves (LeaveManagement admin, MyLeaves teacher)
createLeave (teacher) → sends leave_submitted to admins.

updateLeaveStatus (admin) → sends leave_status_update to the teacher.

14. Purchase Orders (PurchaseOrders page, POForm)
createPO (if status is "Final") and updatePOStatus (when set to "Final") → sends po_sent to the vendor and a system_announcement to admins.

15. Purchase Invoices (PurchaseInvoices page, PurchaseInvoiceForm)
createPurchaseInvoice (if status is "Final") and finalizePurchaseInvoice → sends pi_received to admins.

16. Invoices (Invoices page, InvoiceForm)
createInvoice (if status is "Final") and finalizeInvoice → sends invoice notification (via system_announcement) to the student/parent.

finalizeCreditNote, finalizeDebitNote → sends a system_announcement to admins.

17. Salary Generation (GenerateSalaries page)
generateTeacherSalary → sends salary_slip to the teacher.

18. Progress Evaluations (ProgressEvaluations page)
createProgressEvaluation → sends a progress summary (via system_announcement) to the student/parent.

19. Vouchers (Vouchers page)
createVoucher → sends a system_announcement to admins.

20. Finance – Profit/Loss, etc. (not directly email‑triggering, but you can manually call sendAttendanceReportEmail from report pages)